### criando um usuario completo com SENHA
POST http://localhost:3000/user/ HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "name": "Gabriel Vieira",
  "cpf": "12345678800",
  "email": "gabi@test.com",
  "password": "1234567",
  "type": "ADMIN",
  "status": "ATIVO",
  "birthDate": "1995-05-10T00:00:00.000Z"
}

### TESTE DE ERRO 1: Criando usuário com TIPO INEXISTENTE (TEACHER)
POST http://localhost:3000/user/ HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "name": "Kevin Valido",
  "cpf": "12345678911",
  "email": "kevin@email.com",
  "type": "TEACHER",
  "status": "INATIVO",
  "birthDate": "2005-05-10T00:00:00.000Z"
}

### TESTE DE ERRO 2: Criando usuário com NOME SENDO NÚMERO (Inválido)
POST http://localhost:3000/user/ HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "name": 12345,
  "cpf": "12345678911",
  "email": "kevin@email.com",
  "type": "ADMIN",
  "status": "ATIVO"
}

### TESTE DE ERRO 3: Criando usuário com NOME COM LETRAS INSUFICIENTES OU CARACTERES ESPECIAIS
POST http://localhost:3000/user/ HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "name": "A_",
  "cpf": "12345678911",
  "email": "kevin@email.com",
  "type": "ADMIN",
  "status": "ATIVO"
}

